.TH dysize 3 2023-02-05 "Linux man-pages 6.03"
.SH NAME
dysize \- get number of days for a given year
.SH LIBRARY
Standard C library
.RI ( libc ", " \-lc )
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B "#include <time.h>"
.PP
.BI "int dysize(int " year );
.fi
.PP
.RS -4
Feature Test Macro Requirements for glibc (see
.BR feature_test_macros (7)):
.RE
.PP
.BR dysize ():
.nf
    Since glibc 2.19:
        _DEFAULT_SOURCE
    glibc 2.19 and earlier:
        _BSD_SOURCE || _SVID_SOURCE
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The function returns 365 for a normal year and 366 for a leap year.
The calculation for leap year is based on:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
(year) %4 == 0 && ((year) %100 != 0 || (year) %400 == 0)
.EE
.in
.PP
The formula is defined in the macro
.I __isleap(year)
also found in
.IR <time.h> .
